{
  "text": "Chair-Rise-The time it took to move from a starting seated position to standing upright and returning to the seated position 5 times as rapidly as possible with subject's arms across their chest and feet flat on the floor, was recorded to the nearest 0.01 second. [CITATION_1] Habitual and Maximal Gait Velocities-Subjects were instructed to walk 10 meters at their normal and maximal velocity, which was assessed using an Ultra timer (DCPB Electronics). [CITATION_2] ",
